{"PLOC":[{"def":"A mixture of hair and tar for covering the bottom of a ship.","pos":""}],"PLOCE":[{"def":"A figure in which a word is separated or repeated by way of emphasis, so as not only to signify the individual thing denoted by it, but also its peculiar attribute or quality; as, \"His wife's a wife indeed.","pos":""}],"PLOD":[{"def":"To travel slowly but steadily; to trudge.","pos":""},{"def":"To toil; to drudge; especially, to study laboriously and patiently.","pos":""}],"PLODDER":[{"def":"One who plods; a drudge.","pos":""}],"PLODDING":[{"def":"Progressing in a slow, toilsome manner; characterized by laborious diligence; as, a plodding peddler; a plodding student; a man of plodding habits.","pos":""}],"PLONGE":[{"def":"To cleanse, as open drains which are entered by the tide, by stirring up the sediment when the tide ebbs.","pos":""}],"PLONGEE":[{"def":"A slope or sloping toward the front; as, the plongée of a parapet; the plongée of a shell in its course.","pos":""}],"PLOP":[{"def":"To fall, drop, or move in any way, with a sudden splash or slap, as on the surface of water.","pos":""}],"PLOT":[{"def":"A plan or draught of a field, farm, estate, etc.","pos":""}],"PLOT-PROOF":[{"def":"Secure against harm by plots.","pos":""}],"PLOTFUL":[{"def":"Abounding with plots.","pos":""}],"PLOTINIAN":[{"def":"Of pertaining to the Plotinists or their doctrines.","pos":""}],"PLOTINIST":[{"def":"A disciple of Plotinus, a celebrated Platonic philosopher of the third century, who taught that the human soul emanates from the divine Being, to whom it reunited at death.","pos":""}],"PLOTTER":[{"def":"One who plots or schemes; a contriver; a conspirator; a schemer.","pos":""}],"PLOUTER":[{"def":"To wade or move about with splashing; to dabble; also, to potter; trifle; idle.","pos":""}],"PLOVER":[{"def":"Any one of numerous species of limicoline birds belonging to the family Charadridæ, and especially those belonging to the subfamily Charadrinsæ.","pos":""},{"def":"Any grallatorial bird allied to, or resembling, the true plovers, as the crab plover (Dromas ardeola); the American upland, plover (Bartramia longicauda); and other species of sandpipers.","pos":""}],"PLOY":[{"def":"To form a column from a line of troops on some designated subdivision; -- the opposite of deploy.","pos":""}],"PLOYMENT":[{"def":"The act or movement of forming a column from a line of troops on some designated subdivision; -- the opposite of deployment.","pos":""}]}